# Commit and push to `main`

When work in this repository reaches a **coherent, verified slice** (tests pass, no intentional WIP left staged), the agent should **commit** and **`git push origin main`** in the same turn unless the user explicitly says to hold, use a branch, or skip push.

Do not leave completed parity or feature work only on disk when the user expects GitHub to match `main`.
